PROMPT oracle_bone_divination_record_structure
WITH BUDGET 6000 tokens
USING MODEL "claude-sonnet-4-5"

SELECT
    system_role("You are a Chinese paleography and oracle bone studies expert specializing in the structural analysis of Shang dynasty divination records, the classification of oracle bone inscription elements, and the interpretation of complete bǔcí formulaic patterns.")

GENERATE
    explain_buci_structure("Explain the typical structure of a complete oracle bone divination record (卜辞 bǔcí). Cover: 1) The standard four-part structure of complete divination records including preface (前辞), charge (命辞), prognostication (占辞), and verification (验辞), 2) The preface section containing temporal information such as the sexagenary day date, the name or title of the diviner performing the ceremony, and sometimes additional contextual details about the divination session, 3) The charge section presenting the actual question or statement being divined, typically introduced by formulaic phrases and containing the specific matter requiring divine guidance such as military campaigns, weather, sacrifices, or royal health, 4) The prognostication section recording the diviner's interpretation of the crack patterns as either auspicious (吉) or inauspicious (凶), often with additional qualitative assessments, 5) The verification section documenting the actual historical outcome when available, allowing comparison between the divine prediction and real events, 6) Common formulaic language and standard phrases used in each section including temporal markers, divination terminology, and outcome descriptors, 7) Variations in completeness with many oracle bones preserving only partial records due to the practical constraints of space, time, and the specific purposes of individual divination sessions, 8) The relationship between the physical crack patterns created by heat application and the textual interpretation recorded in the prognostication, 9) Examples of well-preserved complete bǔcí that illustrate all four structural elements, particularly those concerning royal activities, weather predictions, and military decisions, 10) How the standardized structure reflects the institutionalized nature of Shang dynasty divination practices and the systematic approach to recording divine communications, 11) The paleographic and linguistic features that help scholars identify and classify different structural elements even in fragmentary inscriptions.")
WITH OUTPUT BUDGET 3000 tokens, TEMPERATURE 0.1, FORMAT markdown;